<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">438.00/382</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-02-23"><hi rend="italic">February 23,
                                    1926</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received March 3.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 718</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the
                            Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs of the Haitian Government,
                            informs me that in view <pb facs="0525" n="429" xml:id="pg_429"/> of the
                            recent exchange of notes between the Haitian Minister at Washington and
                            the Department of State, the Claims Commission has been informed of the
                            provisions of the Haitian-French Agreement of June 12, 1925, for the
                            regulations of the claims of French citizens and those under French
                            protection. He also informs me that the above named agreement was
                            sanctioned by the National Assembly in the session of February 17,
                            1926.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John H. Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>